To further validate the improved Li dendrites blocking ability, the morphology of the cycled Li anodes paired with PI-PEO-SN and PEO-SN CPEs is carefully scrutinized by SEM as illustrated in Fig. 5c-d. Vividly, a significant number of Li dendrites resulting from inhomogeneous Li deposition can be observed on the surface of the Li anode after cycling in Li/PEO-SN/Li cell. Similarly, the uneven Li deposition also can be detected in Li/PI-PEO/Li symmetric cell (
                        Figure S6
                     ). Conversely, after cycling 1000 h, the surface of Li anode paired with PI-PEO-SN CPEs is still flat and smooth without Li dendrites. Therefore, as demonstrated in Fig. 5e, on the one hand, the introduced 3D PI frameworks with high modulus play the important role to enhance the mechanical strength of PI-PEO-SN CPEs, thereby significantly suppressing Li dendrites formation; on the other hand, SN endows PI-PEO-SN CPEs with good interface compatibility, facilitating uniform Li deposition.
